name: Nike SB Dunk Low Blue Raspberry
Wmns Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Easter'
story: The women’s Air Jordan 5 ‘Easter’ gives the classic silhouette a pastel makeover in keeping with the springtime holiday. Finished in Regal Pink, the smooth nubuck upper features traditional AJ5 elements, including TPU eyelets, lace locks, and quarter-panel netting. Embroidered Jumpman branding lands on the heel overlay and pale green padded tongue. Inside the shoe, the sockliner displays vibrant bands of color in a nod to the tradition of dyed Easter eggs. The sneaker sits atop an Air-assisted polyurethane midsole, accented with speckled shark-tooth detailing and supported by a green-tinged translucent rubber outsole that glows in the dark.

name: Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Military Black'
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Military Black’ showcases the same color blocking and materials featured on the OG ‘Military Blue’ colorway from 1989. Smooth white leather is utilized on the upper, bolstered with a forefoot overlay in grey suede. Contrasting black accents make their way to the TPU eyelets, molded heel tab, and the Jumpman logo displayed on the woven tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a two-tone polyurethane midsole, enhanced with a visible Air-sole unit under the heel.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Stage Haze
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Stage Haze’ features neutral tones on the foundational sneaker that started it all. The upper combines a white leather base with a grey suede heel overlay and a forefoot overlay in cracked black leather. Matching black accents settle on the signature Swoosh and a retro Wings logo stamped on the lateral ankle. Nike branding is outlined in Bleached Coral on the woven tongue tag, delivering a subtle flash of color. The high-top rests on a rubber cupsole that pairs white sidewalls with a grey rubber outsole.

name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low '72-10'
story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘72-10’ brings back a celebratory design theme first featured on an Air Jordan 11 release from 2015. Like its predecessor, this pair nods to the Chicago Bulls’ legendary 1996-96 season, when Michael Jordan led the team to a record-breaking 72-10 record. Rendered in low-top form, the sneaker makes use of a black tumbled leather upper with a tonal patent leather mudguard. Crimson Jumpman branding delivers color-popped accents on the tongue and heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white Phylon midsole, fitted with full-length Air-sole cushioning and supported by a translucent rubber midsole. The Jordan 11 Low '72-10' will release on May 14, 2022.

name: adidas Yeezy 500 Granite
story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Granite’ updates the retro-inspired lifestyle runner with a subdued greyscale finish. Stripped of conspicuous branding, the upper combines charcoal-colored mesh with tonal suede and leather overlays. The collar is lined in padded Lycra for a comfortable fit, while a seamless rubber mudguard offers improved durability. The sneaker sits atop a podular adiPRENE+ midsole inspired by the adidas KB8 3, a Kobe Bryant signature model originally released in 1999.

name: Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Infrared'
story: Built for a new generation of Michael Jordan fans, the Air Jordan 4 Retro TD ‘Red Thunder’ showcases the same color blocking that appeared on the original AJ4 ‘Thunder’ from 2006. This scaled-down version employs a black nubuck upper with contrasting crimson accents on the leather eyelets, mesh quarter panel, and lightweight foam midsole. White Jumpman branding embellishes the tongue, heel overlay, and rubber outsole, featuring a traditional herringbone tread.

name: A-Cold-Wall x Aeon Active CX 'Black Apple Green'
Jordan 4 Retro Infrared
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Infrared’ features distinctive color blocking that recalls the ‘Green Glow’ AJ4 release from 2013. The upper is crafted from smooth nubuck in a charcoal finish. A lighter shade of grey distinguishes the forefoot overlay, while black accents land on the quarter panel netting, structural wings and Jumpman-branded heel tab. The sneaker’s titular hue lights up the woven tongue tag and a quartet of molded eyelets. A polyurethane midsole packs visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel for a smooth ride.

name: Air Jordan 4 Retro PS 'Infrared'
story: Made for little kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS ‘Red Thunder’ showcases the same two-tone color blocking seen on the OG ‘Thunder’ release from 2006. This pair utilizes a black nubuck upper with contrasting crimson accents on the leather eyelets, mesh quarter panel, and full-length foam midsole. Exterior branding is limited to a white Jumpman logo on the tongue and molded heel panel. Underfoot, a herringbone-traction rubber outsole provides superior grip.

name: Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS)
story: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS ‘Infrared’ adds color-popped accents to an otherwise neutral colorway of the vintage silhouette designed by Tinker Hatfield. The color blocking is reminiscent of the ‘Green Glow’ Air Jordan 4 from 2013, and features a dark grey nubuck upper with solid black accents on the quarter panel netting, structural wings, and Jumpman-branded heel piece. A lighter shade of grey distinguishes the forefoot overlay, while vibrant hits of Infrared settle on the molded eyelets and woven Jumpman tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an exposed Air-sole unit nestled in the heel of the two-tone midsole.

name: Jordan 6 Retro Midnight Navy (2022) (GS)
story: The 2022 reissue of the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS ‘Midnight Navy’ brings back a 2000 colorway in big kid sizing. The build is faithful to the original, highlighted by a white leather upper with perforated detailing throughout the midfoot and padded collar. Navy accents appear on the molded tongue, spoiler-like heel tab, and the Jumpman branding hits that decorate the back heel and textile lace guard. The sneaker rests on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, fitted with an Air-sole unit in the heel and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 6 Retro Midnight Navy (2022)
story: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Midnight Navy’ brings back a classic two-tone colorway initially released in 2000. The legacy silhouette sports a white leather upper with perforated detailing throughout the midfoot and collar. Navy blue accents land on the signature windowed tongue, molded heel tab, and the Jumpman branding hits that decorate the lace guard and back heel. The sneaker rides on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, enhanced with a visible Air-sole heel unit and supported by a translucent rubber outsole. The Jordan 6 'Midnight Navy' 2022 will release on May 25, 2022.

name: Dunk Low 'Toasty - Sequoia'
story: Launching as part of the ‘Toasty’ collection, the Nike Dunk Low Next Nature ‘Sequoia’ delivers a winterized version of the classic silhouette. A dark green hue permeates the upper, lined in fleece and featuring synthetic suede overlays atop a quilted textile base made with 100% recycled polyester. Contrasting orange accents make their way to the textured leather Swoosh and a heel tab marked with embroidered Nike branding. A pinwheel logo on the woven tongue tag indicates a sustainable build, one that incorporates 20% recycled content by weight.

name: Air Jordan 9 BG 'Chile Red'
story: The Air Jordan 9 Retro GS ‘Chile Red’ delivers a fiery colorway of the vintage 1993 silhouette in big kid sizing. Speed lacing secures the crimson textile upper, accented with decorative stitching and overlaid with tonal patent leather throughout the collar, mudguard and heel. The latter features an embroidered 23 and a Jumpman logo superimposed atop a globe — a nod to Michael Jordan’s emergence as an international icon. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a color-matched foam midsole, supported underfoot by a durable black rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 9 Retro Chile Red
story: The Air Jordan 9 Retro ‘Chile Red’ features a saturated design that recalls the ‘Motorboat Jones’ colorway from 2012. Stitched crimson textile is utilized on the upper, secured with a speed lacing system and bolstered with tonal patent leather along the mudguard, collar and heel. Contrasting black accents land on an Air Jordan tongue tag, molded eyelets and a prominent pull loop at the heel. The sneaker rides on a glossy red polyurethane midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Air-sole units in the forefoot and heel. The Jordan 9 'Chile Red' will release on May 27, 2022.

name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Green Bean' 2022
story: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 5 ‘Green Bean’ brings back a distinctive two-tone colorway initially released in 2006. Like the original, the mid-top carries a light grey nubuck upper entirely coated in a reflective finish. Bright green accents make their way to the interior lining and the embroidered Jumpman logo that decorate the heel and tongue. The vivid hue is repeated on the shark-tooth detailing that enlivens the dark grey polyurethane midsole. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-tread rubber outsole provides grippy traction. The Jordan 5 'Green Bean' 2022 will release on May 7, 2022.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Paisley Brown
story: The Nike Dunk Low Pro Premium SB ‘Paisley’ treats the retro sneaker to a vintage-fashion makeover. Rendered in a blend of green, pink, blue, and brown hues, an allover paisley print permeates the textile upper, trimmed in brown leather piping and designed to tear away over time, revealing an off-white suede underlay. Branding elements include a white leather Swoosh and an embroidered Nike wordmark on the brown leather heel tab. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

name: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Desert Elephant'
story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Desert Elephant’ showcases materials and color blocking that stay true to the iconic silhouette’s original 1988 release. The upper is constructed from black tumbled leather with signature elephant-print overlays in a light tan finish. The neutral hue is repeated on the collar, eyestay, and tongue, the latter accented with a crimson Jumpman logo. Supporting the mid-top is a white polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit nestled under the heel.

name: A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP
story: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP reunites the Atlanta-based retailer with Jordan Brand for collaboration no. 3. This elevated take on the AJ2 showcases an off-white cracked leather upper with burgundy piping and a translucent heel counter that extends into the midfoot. ‘Maniére’ is stamped in white lettering on the burgundy leather heel tab. Contrasting black accents settle on the laces, quilted interior lining and tongue, featuring snakeskin detailing and a retro Wings logo. The black snakeskin motif is repeated on the midsole — an exotic touch that nods to the OG Air Jordan 2 from 1986, which was made in Italy and featured a subtle reptilian texture on the leather upper. The A Ma Maniére x Jordan 2 will release on April 29, 2022.

name: Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Brave Blue'
story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Brave Blue’ brings back a two-tone palette originally featured on a low-top release from 1988 (and later reissued in 2017). The upper combines blue mesh overlays with a black tumbled leather forefoot and matching black synthetic suede throughout the midfoot and heel. An embroidered blue Jumpman embellishes the tongue, while the 13’s holographic cat eye adorns the lateral collar. Underfoot, the panther paw outsole is equipped with herringbone rubber pods for stop-and-go traction. The Jordan 13 'Brave Blue' will release on April 30, 2022.

name: Air Max 90 Leather TD 'Air Sprung - Iron Grey'
Wmns Air Jordan 11 Retro Low 'Pure Violet'
story: The women’s Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘Pure Violet’ features a spring-ready two-tone palette, rendered in classic color blocking that recalls the original spate of low-top releases from 2001. Fed through webbing eyelets, rope laces secure a white ballistic mesh upper with a glossy patent leather overlay in a pastel lavender hue. The white Phylon midsole, enhanced with full-length Nike Air cushioning, is supported by a carbon fiber spring plate and a translucent rubber outsole. The Wmns Jordan 11 Low 'Pure Violet' will release on April 28, 2022.

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Luxe Burnt Sunrise
Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Crater Purple'
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Anthracite
story: The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort ‘Multi-Color’ showcases color-popped accents on a high-top silhouette inspired by a sneaker icon. The upper combines a white leather base with a die-cut Swoosh and suede forefoot and heel overlays in black and University Gold. Exposed foam is utilized on the tongue and deconstructed collar, featuring two free-floating foam panels with a textile outer layer in Washed Teal. A retro Jordan Wings logo is stamped on the red suede collar flap. The sneaker rests on a rubber midsole enhanced with Zoom Air cushioning in the heel for an extra-comfortable ride.

name: Nike Air Force 1 High '07 SP Billie Eilish Mushroom
Nike ACG Mountain Fly Low Gore-Tex SE Dark Smoke Grey
colorway: Dark Smoke Grey/Iron Grey-Dark Smoke Grey

name: ACG Mountain Fly Low GTX SE 'Hazel Rush'
story: The Nike ACG Mountain Fly Low GTX SE ‘Hazel Rush’ showcases earth tones on a rugged silhouette built to handle harsh terrain and weather conditions. Easy-to-cinch coral rope laces secure the dark khaki textile upper, featuring bootie-style construction and a waterproof Gore-Tex membrane. A reflective grid pattern delivers enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a speckled Nike React midsole, supported by a lugged rubber outsole that wraps up the toe for improved traction and durability.

name: UNO x Zoom Freak 3 NRG '50th Anniversary - Blue'
Air Jordan 7 Retro SE 'Sapphire'
story: The Air Jordan 7 Retro SE ‘Sapphire’ celebrates the 30th anniversary of the classic silhouette with refreshed colors and a revamped build. A muted pink hue is applied to the layered nubuck upper, featuring semi-translucent mesh on the quarter panel and collar. A neoprene inner sleeve in Sapphire and pink provides a snug, comfortable fit, while a webbing pull tab at the heel delivers easy on and off. The mid-top is mounted on a speckled grey foam midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning. The Jordan 7 'Sapphire' will release on April 16, 2022.

name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur
story: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Sulfur’ showcases a yellowish beige hue throughout the one-piece EVA foam build, featuring strategically placed vents throughout the vamp and side panels for maximum breathability. Inside the slip-on, the footbed is equipped with a textured surface that prevents the foot from slipping. Branding is limited to ‘FOAM RNNR’ debossed on the interior collar and an adidas logo on the contoured outsole, featuring a wavy traction pattern for optimal grip.

name: Union LA x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP 'Rattan'
story: The Union LA x Air Jordan 2 Retro SP ‘Rattan’ gives the iconic silhouette a comprehensive makeover, highlighted by a tan textile upper with tonal suede overlays. Perforated detailing on the quarter panel reveals an amber underlay, matching the sneaker’s molded eyelets and an attached ‘UN/LA’ tag. Additional branding elements include a woven Jumpman tag on the exposed foam tongue, along with an embossed Nike wordmark on the heel tab. A retro Wings logo decorates a woven tag affixed to the lateral collar. The sneaker is mounted on a cream-colored polyurethane midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning. The Union x Jordan 2 'Rattan' will release on April 15, 2022.

name: adidas NMD V3 White Red Blue (GS)
Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Ale Brown Sanddrift (W)
Union LA x Jordan Crater Slide 'Grey Fog'
adidas ZX 8000 Kawasaki Ninja
colorway: Semi Solar Green/Semi Solar Green/Bright Blue
story: Taken from a two-piece pack modeled after the Japanese sportbike, the Kawasaki Ninja x adidas ZX 8000 ‘White Green’ showcases a vibrant color palette on the vintage running shoe. White perforated leather is utilized on the upper, bolstered with a chrome heel clip and contrasting leather overlays in marine blue and lime green. Traditional three-stripe branding is replaced by an embroidered ‘Ninja’ wordmark on the lateral side of the left shoe and the medial panel of the right. The sculpted midsole packs Boost cushioning for a smooth, responsive ride.

name: Smiley x Classic Leather Pump '50th Anniversary'
adidas ZX 5K Boost Kawasaki Ninja
story: Launching as part of a two-piece pack inspired by the Japanese sportbike, the Kawasaki Ninja x adidas ZX 5000 Boost ‘Black Green’ delivers a sleek colorway of the progressive lifestyle runner. The upper is constructed from black textile with stitched three-stripes, a polished chrome heel counter, and ‘Ninja’ inscribed in bright green script on the lateral forefoot. Mismatched tongue tags display an adidas Trefoil on the left shoe and Kawasaki branding on the right. The sneaker rides on a responsive Boost midsole, wrapped in a semi-translucent cage and supported by a durable rubber outsole.

name: Air Trainer 1 'Honeydew'
story: The Nike Air Trainer 1 ‘Honeydew’ delivers a modern, utilitarian take on the groundbreaking training shoe originally released in 1987. Neutral grey and beige tones are executed throughout the layered upper, featuring an eclectic blend of canvas, nubuck, leather, and translucent TPU. A pale green Swoosh provides a subtle pop of color, while reflective detailing offers enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. Heritage details remain intact, including a padded mid-cut collar, adjustable midfoot strap, and a lateral outrigger on the cream-colored foam midsole.

name: adidas Adizero Avanti Tyo Tinman Elite
Nike Air Max 95 Medium Blue
story: The Nike Air Max 95 ‘Black Medium Blue’ showcases a traditional gradient finish on the retro running shoe inspired by the human anatomy. The upper is marked by wavy suede and leather overlays in neutral a blend of Anthracite, Cool Grey, and off-white tones. Royal blue accents land on the Air Max tongue tag and webbing eyelets, featuring reflective detailing for added visibility in low-light conditions. The sneaker rides on a white polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the forefoot and heel.

name: adidas Ozelia Guardians of the Galaxy Gamora
